

LOAD
To Load the data from the
file system (local/HDFS) into a relation.

 a = load
'/hadoopdata/pig/A.txt' using PigStorage(',') as (a1:int, a2:int, a3:int);

 

STORE

To save a relation to the
file system (local/HDFS).

 STORE l INTO '/pigoutput';

 

DUMP

To print the contents of a
relation on the console.

Dump a ;

FOREACH

To generate data
transformations based on columns of data.

l = FOREACH c GENERATE a1, a2, a2*a3;

 

FILTER

To remove unwanted rows
from a relation.

f = FILTER c by $1 > 3;

 

GROUP BY 

To group the data in a
single relation.

g = GROUP c by $2;
g = GROUP c by ($0,$1); 
h = GROUP c ALL;

ORDER BY 

To arrange a relation in a
sorted order based on one or more fields (ascending or descending).

f = order c by a1 desc ;

 DESCRIBE

To describe the schema of
a relation.

describe f;

